## Example 1: Pace — Engine Hum Swell

**Cue ID:** aud-engine-swell

**Section Anchor:** s41-inspection-end

**Purpose:** pace (brief tension lift after inspection scene)

**Cue Type:** ambience

**Cue Description:** Low, steady engine hum swells, then eases

**Placement:** Under final two lines of section; fade by choice list

**Intensity/Duration:** Soft; 3-4 seconds; no sharp transients

**Text Equivalent:** "[A low engine hum rises, then settles.]"

**Safety Notes:** Avoid sudden onset; safe range 60-85 dB SPL; gradual fade prevents startle

**Motif Ties:** Industrial-dock motif (established in Act 1 arrival scene)

**Inclusion Criteria:** Only when section mentions freight engines or dock machinery

**Localization Notes:** N/A (non-verbal cue)

**Reproducibility Requirement (off-surface):** "Log session tempo, key bed (engine loop source), gain automation envelope"

**Spoiler Risk:** low (no narrative reveals; atmospheric only)

**Status:** planned

---

## Example 2: Signpost — Alarm Chirps

**Cue ID:** aud-alarm-checkpoint

**Section Anchor:** s41-dock-gate

**Purpose:** signpost (checkpoint context; reduce reader hesitation about security moment)

**Cue Type:** stinger

**Cue Description:** Short alarm chirps twice, distant

**Placement:** Between prose lines; 1 second before "The foreman approaches"

**Intensity/Duration:** Brief (0.5 sec each chirp); low-medium intensity; spaced 1 sec apart

**Text Equivalent:** "[A short alarm chirps twice, distant.]"

**Safety Notes:** Brief duration prevents fatigue; distant placement reduces startle; chirps not harsh

**Motif Ties:** Security-alert motif (used at all access points to build recognition)

**Inclusion Criteria:** Show when section involves security checkpoints or access control

**Localization Notes:** N/A (non-verbal; alarm is culturally universal)

**Reproducibility Requirement (off-surface):** "Log alarm sample source, pitch shift (+200 cents), reverb send (distant preset), spacing timing"

**Spoiler Risk:** low (establishes context only; no plot reveals)

**Status:** planned

---

## Example 3: Mood — Station Ambient

**Cue ID:** aud-station-ambient

**Section Anchor:** s12-arrival

**Purpose:** mood (establish industrial atmosphere and scale; player's first audio impression of station)

**Cue Type:** ambience

**Cue Description:** Distant machinery hum, occasional metal creaks, ventilation whisper

**Placement:** Loop under entire opening section (fade in at section start, fade out at first dialogue line)

**Intensity/Duration:** Very low (barely perceptible); 45 seconds seamless loop; subtle internal variations

**Text Equivalent:** "[Distant machinery hums; metal settles; air circulates.]"

**Safety Notes:** Very low intensity prevents listener fatigue; no sudden changes within loop; smooth crossfade prevents jarring transition

**Motif Ties:** Industrial-station baseline (establishes environmental tone for all interior scenes)

**Inclusion Criteria:** Chapter opening; sets emotional baseline for act; first view of station interior

**Localization Notes:** N/A (non-verbal environmental sound)

**Reproducibility Requirement (off-surface):** "Full mix log: machinery layer (source file, EQ), creak layer (timing map, randomization seed), vent layer (filter curve), loop crossfade points (samples), overall gain (-18 dBFS)"

**Spoiler Risk:** low (establishes setting only; no narrative information)

**Status:** producing (assigned to Audio Producer)

